    <description>
thresh is a lightweight, 12 MB native binary that provisions WSL2 Linux environments from declarative YAML blueprints.

Features:
- Native AOT compilation (12 MB, zero dependencies)
- WSL2 integration for environment provisioning
- 12 built-in Linux distributions (Ubuntu, Alpine, Debian, Fedora, Rocky)
- AI-powered blueprint generation (OpenAI GPT-4o-mini)
- Blueprint-based environment configuration
- Custom distribution support
- Interactive AI chat mode

Requirements:
- Windows 11 with WSL2 enabled
- .NET runtime NOT required (self-contained Native AOT binary)
    </description>
